revision.text:
The '''1899-1900 season''' was the fifth competitive season in [[Belgium|Belgian]] [[football (soccer)|football]].
==Overview== Only one official division existed at the time, split into two leagues. It was called ''Coupe de Championnat'' (Championship Cup) and its winner was decided after a two-legged final match between the winners of each league.
At the end of the season it was decided to merge the two league in one. Antwerp F.C. withdrew from the league after nearly every player left the club for the new [[K. Beerschot V.A.C.|Beerschot]] and [[K.V. Kortrijk|F.C. Courtraisien]] was relegated. The clubs that replaced those two were Beerschot and [[R.C.S. Verviétois|Verviers F.C.]].
