{{Infobox television |show_name = ABC Funfit |image = |caption = |aka = |genre = Children's program |creator = |writer = Donna Bond |director = Bill Fertik |creat_director = |developer = |presenter = |starring = [[Mary Lou Retton]] |voices = |narrated = |theme_composer = |opentheme = |endtheme = |composer = [[Michael Zager]] |country = [[United States]] |language = [[English language|English]] |num_seasons = |num_episodes = |list_episodes = |exec_producer = |co_exec = |producer = [[Eleanor Sanger|Eleanor Sanger Riger]] |sup_producer = |asst_producer = |cons_producer = |co-producer = |editor = |story_editor = |location = |cinematography = |camera_setup = |runtime = 5 minutes |network = [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] |picture_format = Color |audio_format = |first_run = |first_aired = {{Start date|1985|9|7}} |last_aired = {{End date|1985|12|7}} |preceded_by = |followed_by = |related = |website = |prod_website = }}
'''''ABC Funfit''''' is a series of short American television segments that were broadcast in 1985 and aired twice a day during [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]]'s [[Saturday-morning cartoon|Saturday morning cartoon]] programs. The segments were five minutes long and presented exercises and information to promote children's [[physical fitness]]. Olympic gold medalist [[Mary Lou Retton]] hosted the series, assisted by the "Funfit Kids" (Ericka Pazcoquin, [[Brad Kane|Bradley Kane]], Melissa Kern and Efrain Bracero). The show was choreographed by [[Lynne Taylor-Corbett]].<ref>Terrace, Vincent (2009). ''Encyclopedia of Television Shows, 1925 through 2007'' (Volume 1). Jefferson, North Carolina: McFarland & Company, Inc. {{ISBN|978-0-7864-3305-6}}.</ref> The album ''ABC Funfit featuring Mary Lou Retton'' was released in 1985.
