{{coord|21.389387|-158.005779|display=title}} 
'''Hans L'Orange Field''' is a [[stadium]] in [[Waipahu, Hawai'i]].  It is primarily used for [[baseball]], and is the home field of [[Hawaii Pacific University|Hawaii Pacific University's]] men's baseball team, the Sharks. It was the home field of the [[Hawaii Winter Baseball]] teams [[North Shore Honu]]  and [[West Oahu CaneFires]] before the league folded. It holds 2,200 people.

== History ==

Hans L'Orange Field began as a recreation area for Oahu Sugar Co. workers.  Originally known as Oahu Sugar Co. Field, it was later named after the manager who, in 1924, convinced the company to give up several acres of cane field, to create the recreation area.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Honolulu Star-Bulletin]]|date=June 12, 1997|url=http://starbulletin.com/97/06/12/news/story2.html|last1=Ohira|first1=Rod|title=Waipahu Turns 100}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|work=[[Honolulu Star-Bulletin]]|date=October 11, 1999|url=http://starbulletin.com/1999/10/11/news/story5.html|last1=Ohira|first1=Rod|title=Waipahu’s field of dreams marks 75 years}}</ref>

