The '''Raleigh Runnels Memorial Pool''' is an [[Aquatic sports|aquatics]] venue located on the campus of [[Pepperdine University]] in [[Malibu, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pepperdinesports.com/facilities/runnels-pool.html|title=Pepperdine University pool profile|publisher=pepperdinesports.com|accessdate=2018-06-24}}</ref> The pool was constructed in 1975 and dedicated the following year to Raleigh Neal Runnels, the son of Pepperdine Chancellor Dr. [[Charles Runnels]], who died of cancer at 17. 

The pool hosted the [[Water polo at the 1984 Summer Olympics|water polo]] competitions for the [[1984 Summer Olympics]] in neighboring [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1984/1984v1pt1.pdf|title=1984 Summer Olympics official report. Volume 1. Part 1. pp. 147-9.|publisher=la84foundation.org|accessdate=2018-06-24}}</ref> 

