{{Infobox martial art | image = | imagecaption = | name = Women's kickboxing | focus = [[Strike (attack)|Striking]] | hardness = Full-contact | olympic = | country = | creator = | parenthood = [[Karate]], [[Muay Thai]], [[Boxing]] | descendant arts = [[Shoot boxing]] | famous_pract = see [[list of female kickboxers]] }}
'''Women''' have participated in '''[[kickboxing]]''' since the 1960s in Thailand.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gampell.com/boxing.htm|title=Jennifer Gampell|publisher=Gampell.com|accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref> But there has been a superstition and prejudice women have often being prevented from participating in the major tournaments in Thailand.<ref>{{cite news|title= Sugar and Spice and a Vicious Right: Thai Boxing Discovers Its Feminine Side|newspaper=[[The New York Times]]|date=2007-09-16|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2007/09/16/world/asia/16thai1.html?scp=3&sq=muay%20thai&st=cse|accessdate=2016-03-25 | first=Thomas | last=Fuller}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=P-Nv_LUi6KgC&pg=PA322&lpg=PA322&dq=female+muay+thai+thailand&source=bl&ots=I6KHH1jUTJ&sig=Fo-trRk98efwHUvSb0RxAY7KrQI&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiTt4bF-t_LAhXMtBQKHaR_AWo4HhDoAQhDMAY#v=onepage&q=female%20muay%20thai%20thailand&f=false |title=Martial Arts of the World: An Encyclopedia of History and Innovation |page=322 |website=Books.google.co.uk |date= |accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | first=Jennifer | last=Gampell | url= | title= Weekend Journal: Thailand's Boxing Babes- Women Make Their Way Back into the Ring | work=[[The Asian Wall Street Journal]] | date=July 14–16, 2000}}</ref>
The World’s Muay Thai Angels is one of the first organisations to be a place for women to participate in and the first tournament was won by [[Chommanee Sor Taehiran]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Newhall |first=Lindsey |url=http://fightland.vice.com/blog/the-world-muay-thai-angels-marketing-the-women-fighters-of-thailand |title=The World Muay Thai Angels: Marketing the Women Fighters of Thailand &#124; FIGHTLAND |publisher=Fightland.vice.com |date=2015-02-13 |accessdate=2016-03-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.muaythaitv.com/news/chommanee-wins-world-muaythai-angels-n3961.html|title=Chommanee wins World Muaythai Angels|publisher=Muaythaitv.com|accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>
[[Women's kickboxing in Australia]] has a small but devoted following. In the 1970s women in the United States took up kickboxing as they were prevented from taking part in [[women's boxing]].<ref name="smith">{{cite book|last1=Smith|first1=Malissa|title=A History of Women's Boxing|date=2014|publisher=Rowman & Littlefield|isbn=9781442229952|page=124|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=_ErHAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA124&lpg=PA124&dq=history+of+women+kickboxing&source=bl&ots=hEG3MnpFCG&sig=I8YJidPWYh5uJ9uCSsm1el7liws&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiJ-dTIz9LLAhVMaRQKHX4ZABQQ6AEIPzAH#v=onepage&q=history%20of%20women%20kickboxing&f=false|accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref> In the UK kickboxing has a growing following according to the [[World Muay Thai Council|WMC]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=I6qhCgAAQBAJ&pg=PT325&dq=female+muay+thai&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjt3OGnw9LLAhWHQBQKHXmSBG4Q6AEILzAA#v=onepage&q=female%20muay%20thai&f=false|title=Global Perspectives on Women in Combat Sports|publisher=Books.google.co.uk|accessdate=2016-03-31}}</ref>
In May 2016 the kickboxing organisation [[Glory (kickboxing)|Glory]] announced the creation of a women's division built around [[Tiffany van Soest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bloodyelbow.com/2016/5/13/11672222/glory-kickboxing-grand-prix-tournament-womens-division-ufc-fight-pass-tiffany-van-soest|title= Glory announces Grand Prix tournament to launch new women's division|work=bloodyelbow.com}}</ref>
==In popular culture== In [[Stieg Larsson]]'s book ''[[The Girl Who Played with Fire]]'' (2006) and its [[The Girl Who Played with Fire (film)|film adaptation]], [[Lisbeth Salander]], her friend and lover Miriam Wu, and their friend Paolo are kickboxers. Lisbeth adopted her kickboxing ringname, "The Wasp", as her hacker handle and has a wasp tattoo on her neck.
==See also== *[[List of female kickboxers]] *[[Women's kickboxing in Australia]]
